    "body": "If you just concatenate the source files, you might get a different result. Etherscan has to implement a multi-file feature if it wants to verify all contracts. As an example:\r\n\r\na.sol:\r\n```\r\ncontract C {}\r\n```\r\nb.sol:\r\n```\r\nimport \"b.sol\" as X;\r\ncontract C {}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf you concatenate these two files, imports will break and you will get multiple identifiers with the same name.",
